edu.ncsu.csc316.compressor.manager

Class CompressionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc316.compressor.manager.CompressionManager

  • public class CompressionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The CompressionManager class handles behaviors associated with compressing an input file, decompressing an input file, and generating a report of the most frequently used words in an input file. test
    Author:
    Dr. King, Caleb Wiebe, Matt Kierski

    • Method Detail

      • processFile

        public edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.list.List<java.lang.String> processFile(java.lang.String pathToInputFile,
                                                                   java.lang.String outputDirectory)
                                                            throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        Determines whether to compress or decompress the specified input file; creates the output file in the specified output directory; then returns a list of strings that represent each line of the processed output. For example, if the input file is: Baby shark I do not know the rest of this song Then the returned list would be at index 0: Baby shark at index 1: I do not know the rest of this song
        Parameters:
        pathToInputFile - the path to the input file to be processed
        outputDirectory - the directory where the processed file should be saved
        Returns:
        a list of strings that represent the lines of processed output
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - when no file is found

      • getCompressed

        public edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.list.List<java.lang.String> getCompressed(edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.list.List<java.lang.String> fileLines)
        Compresses the input list that represents the specified input file, then returns a list of strings that represent each line of the compressed output. For example, if the file being compressed contains the text: Baby shark I do not know the rest of this song Then the input list would be at index 0: Baby shark at index 1: I do not know the rest of this song
        Parameters:
        fileLines - the list of lines of text in the input file
        Returns:
        a list of strings that represent the compressed output

      • getDecompressed

        public edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.list.List<java.lang.String> getDecompressed(edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.list.List<java.lang.String> fileLines)
        Decompresses the input list that represents the specified input file, then returns a list of strings that represent each line of the decompressed output. For example, if the file being decompressed contains the text: Baby shark I do not know the rest of this song Then the input list would be: at index 0: Baby shark at index 1: I do not know the rest of this song
        Parameters:
        fileLines - the list of lines of text in the input file
        Returns:
        a list of strings that represent the compressed output
